## Acceptance criteria

### Product AC (from pm-to-engineering.md)

> Each AC carries a status suffix for AC change impact analysis (session-start 1a):
> - `[status: pending]` — not yet verified
> - `[status: done]` — verify-full passed and code-review marked done
> - `[status: superseded]` — withdrawn by an upstream supersedes; evidence no longer authoritative

- AC-F01-001: [stable testable description] [status: pending]
- AC-F01-002: [stable testable description] [status: pending]
- AC-F01-003: [stable testable description] [status: pending]

### Backend AC (produced in Phase 2, verified in Phase 3)

> BAC-<feature>-<sequence> is produced by api-implementation / data-layer in Phase 2.
> It may reference a related product AC, but never inherits or reuses that AC's number.
> BAC uses the same status suffix as product AC.

- BAC-F01-001: [backend testable description, e.g., "POST /todos returns 201"] [status: pending]
- BAC-F01-002: [backend testable description, e.g., "GET /todos/:id returns 404 for unknown id"] [status: pending]

### Integration AC (produced and verified in Phase 3)

> IAC-<feature>-<sequence> is produced by mock-to-real-switch / contract-verify / e2e-verification in Phase 3.
> It verifies frontend ↔ backend contract consistency and end-to-end user flows.
> IAC uses the same status suffix as product AC.

- IAC-F01-001: [integration testable description, e.g., "E2E create-todo flow passes"] [status: pending]
- IAC-F01-002: [integration testable description, e.g., "frontend mock→real switch succeeds without code changes"] [status: pending]

